name: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat
description: The WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the information returned by calling the WebGLRenderingContext.getShaderPrecisionFormat() method.

members.name: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.rangeMin
members.description: The base 2 log of the absolute value of the minimum value that can be represented.

members.name: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.rangeMax
members.description: The base 2 log of the absolute value of the maximum value that can be represented.

members.name: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.precision
members.description: The number of bits of precision that can be represented. For integer formats this value is always 0.
